    <title>After typing an URL into the URL-bar and pressing the RETURN-Key, the "blinking cursor" jumps into text-fields before loading the new page</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Hello Firefox-Team,</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">when I type an URL into the URL-bar and pressing the RETURN-Key, the "blinking cursor" jumps into text-fields before loading the new page.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">*** 3 6beta4pre + Minefield ***</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">*** See steps to reproduce***</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Thanks and regards
Mehmet</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.2">1 go to www.google.com</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.3">2 click into the URL-Bar (or CMD+L)</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.4">3 type a new URL into the URL-Bar and press RETURN</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">Actual Results:  
The "blinking curser" jumps after pressing the RETURN-key into the search-field of www.google.com before loading the the new page</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="10">
            <sentence id="10.1">Expected Results:  
The "blinking curser" should NOT jump after pressing the RETURN-key into the search-field of www.google.com</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="11">
            <sentence id="11.1">Same happens for example on www.youtube.com</sentence>
        </paragraph>
